Package: curveRweights
Title: Bayesian Precision Weighting from Calibration Curve Uncertainty
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Michael Scot", "Zens", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "michael.s.zens@dartmouth.edu")
Description: Estimates observation-level precision weights from the posterior
    coefficient of variation (pcov) of calibration curve predictions using a
    joint location-scale Bayesian regression model.  The scale submodel
    estimates the power-law relationship sigma_i = phi * pcov_i^beta1, where
    phi captures baseline variance inflation beyond calibration curve
    uncertainty and beta1 captures how steeply pcov drives weight
    differentiation.  A saturated cell-means location model absorbs all
    systematic experimental effects so that the scale parameters are identified
    purely from within-cell residual structure.  Weights w_i = 1/sigma_i^2 are
    then available for downstream weighted least-squares, meta-regression, or
    survey-weighted rank tests comparing experimental conditions.
